    "[Radiography] What are the most probable differential diagnoses for a 49-year-old male patient with recurring bone fractures and infections?Compacted endplates of the vertebral bodies can be seen in the lumbar spine.",
    "[…] Multiple Myeloma: This is a form of bone marrow cancer that can lead to bone pain, fractures, and infections.",
    "An X-ray image canshow \"densified\" areas that are actually due to bone damage.Multiple myeloma typically presents with hyperlucent (instead of \"densified\") bone areas.",
    "[Radiography] A uniform expansion and increased sclerosis of the vertebral body endplates can be seen across the entire spine, with the intervening vertebral body appearing comparatively less sclerotic.",
    "What is the associated radiologic sign called?"
